formatted_address: 10 Tuas Ave 3, #639409 Village Eating House Food Centre, 10, Singapore 639409
name: Tuas Village

reviews.text: Lighting is a bit dim, and carparking is few but food is good. Anak Medan Nasi Padang is very good quality and large portions. Highly recommend

Fresh fruits & old time food stalls... Overall quite good & tasty foods in the industrial areas... Normally after lunch time, most of the stalls will be preparing to close... clean up & preparation for tomorrow... uncle clear the used plates & cups very quickly...üëçüëçüëç
A lot of food variety. Only drink stall very expensive for a hot tea at $1.50 and taste bland. The Lor Mee are still acceptable with big chunky pork.

$4 Nasi Lemak! Looking at the portion given, it's a rare find! Came across this coffee shop and decided to have my Brunch here.. Saw a pax ahead of me left with Nasi lemak in his hands. Looks good. So decided to order it. Gave $10 to the Malay stall Kakak and received $6 back. Thought she returned me extra change... but it is actually only $4! It's a Nasi Padang stall. Maybe will try their nasi padang next.
Bought Fishball Mee for $4.50, with two small slices of mushroom, 4 small slices of fish cake and two fish balls only. So ridiculous qty for the price. Pls dun cheat ppl in selling food.

vicinity: 10 Tuas Avenue 3, #639409 Village Eating House Food Centre, 10, Singapore
